<td width="10"><img src="http://www.maximumeq.com/forum/Images/SmallNew.gif" border="0" alt="New Message"></td><td width="50%"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="EEEEEE"><b>RE:Wish List for Shadowknights (modified 1 times)</b> </font></td><td width="50%" align="RIGHT"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="EEEEEE"><b>Dune</b></font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td><a href="UltraBoard.cgi?Action=ShowProfile&ID=dune&Board=shadow&Idle=30&Sort=0&Order=Descend&Page=0&Session=" target="Profile" OnMouseOver="window.status='View Dune (dune) Profile.';return true;" OnMouseOut="window.status=''"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="000000 ">Profile</font></a></td><td align="RIGHT"></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="EEEEEE">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">This is what I’d like to see done in the near future:<p>

1. Starting with the most popular topic Harm Touch:<br>
a) Damage dealt should be 60% of the SK’s HP’s.<br>
So if you have 500 hp’s the damage dealt to the mob should be about 300 hp’s.<br>
b) Less resisted.<br>
c) Ok maybe 70% of the total HP's at the most. It's not supposed to be a death touch spell.  <br>
   Just extra damage thrown in for good measure.<p>

2. Higher average damage:<br>
With my Dark Reaver I do about 35 damage on average, while my maximum damage is about 68.<br>
The average damage should be higher than this (I’m not expecting to hit for 60 every time though)<br>
A ranger in my group was dealing way more damage than me.<br>
Here is an example of my average fight with a blue mob about 3 levels below me:<br>
Round 1:<br>
You hit x for 35 damage!<br>
You hit x for 2 damage!<br>
Round 2:<br>
You hit x for 10 damage!<br>
You miss your target!<br>
Round 3:<br>
You hit x for 15 damage!<br>
You hit x for 20 damage!<br>
Round 3:<br>
You miss your target!<br>
Round 4:<br>
You miss your target!<br>
Round 5:<br>
You miss your target!<br>
Round 6:<br>
You hit x for 5 damage!<br>
You miss your target!<br>
Round 7:<br>
You hit x for 57 damage!<br>
What gives? This is not unusual. I get similar results for 1hs and 1hb.<br>
I have my skill maxed out for a 35 SK.<p>

3. Our spells are resisted like hell (actually, most spell casters are resisted a lot lately).<br>
Thank you VI for making the game more “FUN”. Death is fun, isn’t it? (just like “640k ought to be enough” quote)<br>
Makes you almost wish to create a pure tank and loose all spell casting ability.<br>
Lower the bloody magic resistance on mobs!<p>

4. Make AC and the bonus statistics  (from magic items) actually worth while.<br>
While back I had my dexterity bumped to over 120. I used to Vampiric Embrace 4 times a fight on average. After the recent patches I get a boner if it goes off once a fight.<br>
So I switch my bonuses for AC. I’ve increased it over 30 points. So here I am thinking that the higher AC will make me harder to damage. Nope, no such luck. I’m still getting hit the same.<br>
And while we’re on the subject of getting hit: I Siphon Strength to lower the mobs STR.<br>
This is what happens to me 90% of the time:<br>
X hits me for 36 damage<br>
X hits me for 72 damage.<br>
And it keeps on hitting me in the 60 to 80 range. I though that Siphon Strength would reduce the mobs STR, that means damage output. But nope. Only for one hit. It gave me more STR. Fine. I can carry more. But my damage output increases by maybe 2 points. This plus my average damage makes me want to hurl.<p>

5. Pet. Just like someone suggested, make the aggro as if the pet was the same level as me. Don’t make the pet the same level just the aggro .This way I could actually use my pet in dungeons or densely populated areas.<br>
Loose the skeleton. It’s what Necromancers have. We’re not Necromancers. We’re evil knights. Lords of hate and fear. Give us a transparent ghost looking pet or as someone suggested a black shadowy figure (clone of ourselves) with glowing eyes.<p>

6. Give us a spell that will makes us look like an undead knight in armor. This spell would also proc FEAR on random. Death knight. Lord of evil. This would be a higher level spell, 40 or so.<p>

I’m not asking for the world here. SK’s (and if you read closely other classes) could benefit from some cool changes. Give a breath of fresh air to a aging game.<br>
Constant  nerfing of all classes and “improvements” to mobs make the game frustrating instead of enjoyable. <br>
