<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">In my opinion Shadowknights have come a long way.  I'll give you some examples.<p>

1. Harm Touch is resisted less often and the damage output has been increased.<p>

2. Lifetap spells have been added to our arsenal of spells, replacing other such spells as Mend Bones and Voice Graft.<p>

3. Many new SHD weapons are available that truly allow us to dominate a battle.<p>

Some of you think this isn't enough, and I'm sure people in general will always want more than what they have.  There is always room for improvement, just don't expect adjustments that make Shadowknights godlike.  We may not have the absolute power in fights, but we have one thing that seems to elude many people: Versatility.<p>

We can use Gather Shadows to travel safer than most, and once you obtain a Circlet of Shadow you don't need the spell mem'd at all and the spell is instantaneous.  We can Feign Death to avoid our own demise or to pull to a group without training.  We can draw HP's from our enemies to heal.  We can reverse kite, by casting a Darkness spell and then Fear eithout taking much damage.  We can debuff enemies with our spells and cause damage in the heat of battle.  We can use Shadow Vortex to taunt enemies off healers or Enchanters without worrying if it will break a "mes" spell.  We have many talents if you know how to use them.<p>

One more thing.  Our pets do suck, but they help in dire situations or in the case you solo.  They only require bone chips and mana, not a bad deal if you ask me.  See you in Norrath.<p>

Synthe Hateblade<br>
Shadowknight of Mythic Legion<br>
Servant of Innoruuk</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
