<td><a href="UltraBoard.cgi?Action=ShowProfile&ID=synthe&Board=shadow&Idle=30&Sort=0&Order=Descend&Page=0&Session=" target="Profile" OnMouseOver="window.status='View Synthe Hateblade (synthe) Profile.';return true;" OnMouseOut="window.status=''"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="000000 ">Profile</font></a></td><td align="RIGHT"></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="EEEEEE">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">I don't want you to think I'm a newbie just tossing out information.  I was basically just stating examples of how a Shadowknight is useful.  Most people just complain on these boards, regardless of class, about how they need this improved or that improved and after they list all the improvements the class would be godlike.  If that's what a person wants, fine.  I wasn't planning on arguing about it, but I'll respond with my opinions.<p>

First, My primary character is a L51 human Shadowknight who worships Innoruuk.  I did not buy my account on Ebay and I've put many hours into developing Synthe, as have most of you with your Shadowknights.<p>

1.  Harm Touch at my level maxes at 621HP direct damage.  We all get resisted, there are no guarantees.  I have had full damage on reds near L55 and also had resists so that HT does minimal damage for 150HP or so.  It's useless against dragons and gods, but that is a rule of the game I agree with.  HT never decreases in damage output, and after a certain level (possibly 44) the calculation of how much damage you do is increased even more.  No, you aren't going to destroy a mob with HT, but you can save the Cleric's life if the mob is pounding on him/her and Divine Aura faded, leaving the Cleric utterly defenseless.  It's a unique ability that should be used wisely.<p>

2.  My SHD is not in his teens, and yes I use my highest available spell in the Lifetap family : Siphon Life (75HP).  I don't rely on it to do damage to an enemy, I use it to do damage to an enemy and heal myself slightly.  It's not a grand way to heal yourself, but it's not entirely useless.  My unbuffed HP are near 1800HP and I always have it mem'd.  You never know when one Lifetap spell is the difference between experience gained and experience lost in a fight until it's over.<p>

3.  I have a few decent weapons, the Mace of the Shadowed Soul being my primary weapon.  I obtained it in a joint guild raid.  No one ever said a single guild has to go alone, and yes luck has it's part no matter what you do.  Anything worth having isn't going to come easy, most of the time.<p>

4.  I realize other classes can use Invisibility, but not all other classes have an item that is not required to be equipped and can cast an instant Gather Shadows spell using no mana.  In fact only two classes share such an item that I know of: Circlet of Shadow.<p>

5.  Feign Death is a very beneficial spell/ability and only three classes have it.  Not everyone can FD pull, and this is yet one more reason why a SHD is versatile.  Of the two tank classes who can Feign Death, Monks & Shadowknights, we have the highest AC.<p>

6.  Darkness is a spell purely based on Magic Resistance and is resisted many times as you know, but it is still a very powerful spell.  We aren't the only class who has resists, and thanks to the fact we are melee primarily it doesn't affect us as much as a Wizard who uses Ice Comet on a mob and only does 250HP damage, because he was resisted.<p>

7.  Pets.  Not much to say.  They suck, end of story.  I use mine to impress newbies and in duels, not much else anymore.  I disagree on your improvements to them, but that's just me.<p>

Overall, I have a positive outlook on my SHD.  I was at it since the first month of release and Verant has truly improved the class to my satisfaction.  Don't forget we are rumored to get disciplines soon.  I know it can be bleak at times.  Remember we are not a simple class to play, and we have many tactics and skills to aid us and our comrades.  See you in Norrath.<p>

Synthe Hateblade<br>
Shadowknight of Mythic Legion<br>
Servant of Innoruuk</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
