<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Dark Greetings all,<br>
My first post, I will try to not get flamed. Being a shabbie knight of the 33rd season I DO see the fun and benefits of being one of the most rare kick arse classes in everquest. But also being a fan of shadow knight forums I see the hurt the 50+ lvls bring. But I cant speak on that.<br>
My wishlist has multiple items. Hows about giving shadow knights a pet snake. Everquest is full of many different snakes classes that have that annoying poison spell that isnt given to younger knights. Ok the damage they do with melee would be insignificant. And the snake pet wouldnt be aggroed by low lvl animal mobs. Ending the horrid dread wolf wanting a bone effect. Of course some mobs would still aggro the thing cause of its lvl but its better than the free pickens pet we got. We would use snake scales instead of bone chips therefore no comp with uber paid necroes. Couple of hits would end the pet but any shabbie knight who is lettin his pet take hits for him aint usin his pet correctly. Enuf on that next wish.<br>
Harm touch. Makes me cringe thinkin about how we are treated with this ability. I love it to death(pun intended) but if we arent going to get equal hp distribution as the pallies then how about a effect of blind at higher lvls. Ok let me explain myself. I asked myself one day why is it our built up death only goes to one days build. I hardly ever use my HT as soon as it pops up on macro. How about the luxury of building our death if wanted for more than one day. On the second day of building we burn the eyeballs in the sockets for a bit(temporary blind). Stops one solitary mob from chasing. Pvp maybe tweak it so it only stuns. I do realize the power we would wield. Pallies could build maybe to the effect of a higher lvl buff than what would usually be gained. I dont know not a pally dont harass me for that ; )<br>
2cp and a bag of chips! Thanks for listening.<hr>Come, tempt me to make the soft brown earth your new home!!!</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
